      • warnings

        public T warnings(List<List<ParseWarning>> warnings)
        Provides a list object that any parser warnings will be put into.
        Parameters:
        warnings - the list object that will be populated with the warnings of each parsed iCalendar object. Each element in the list is a list of warnings for one parsed object. Therefore, the size of this list will be equal to the number of parsed iCalendar objects. If an iCalendar object does not have any warnings, then its warning list will be empty.
        Returns:
        this

      • defaultTimezone

        public T defaultTimezone(TimeZone defaultTimezone)
        Sets the timezone that will be used for parsing date property values that are floating or that have invalid timezone definitions assigned to them. Defaults to TimeZone.getDefault().
        Parameters:
        defaultTimezone - the default timezone
        Returns:
        this
